   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect your laptop to the service port (J405) located
on the rear side of the front panel (A810).</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">Use the service port cable 940â€“0024D for the
proper connection of all required signals.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Launch the UPS Tuner application and click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Next</uicontrol> in the window that appears.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">If the connection fails, you can reconnect, by clicking <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Communication</uicontrol> &gt; <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Connect</uicontrol> in the
top menu bar.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the module you can want to configure: if you want
to configure the HMI, select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Display Module (HMI)</uicontrol>, and if you want to configure the controller box, select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Controller Box</uicontrol>, then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Next.</uicontrol>
            </cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/upstuner_selectmodule_0000117112.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         translate="no"
                         xml:lang="en"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Follow the instructions on your laptop.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">If the connection fails, check the communication ports
via the menu <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Communications</uicontrol> &gt; <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Set
communication parameters</uicontrol> and adjust if needed. All other
parameters are configured automatically to be compatible with the
UPS for both the HMI and the controller box.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
      </steps>
